d turn's checkpoint would contain only the first turn's messages, silently losing transcript data. The \\\"file already exists\\\" shortcut was intended for integration tests but fires in production too.\\n<!-- DESCRIPTION END -->\\n\\n<!-- BUGBOT_BUG_ID: ref1_086a4f8d-3a72-435d-8f5a-cc01b5b2d077 -->\\n\\n<!-- LOCATIONS START\\ncmd/entire/cli/agent/opencode/lifecycle.go#L124-L128\\nLOCATIONS END -->\\n<p><a href=\\\"https://cursor.com/open?REDACTED\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\"><picture><source media=\\\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\\\" srcset=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-cursor-dark.png\\\"><source media=\\\"(prefers-color-scheme: light)\\\" srcset=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-cursor-light.png\\\"><img alt=\\\"Fix in Cursor\\\" width=\\\"115\\\" height=\\\"28\\\" src=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-cursor-dark.png\\\"></picture></a>&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://cursor.com/agents?REDACTED\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\"><picture><source media=\\\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\\\" srcset=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-web-dark.png\\\"><source media=\\\"(prefers-color-scheme: light)\\\" srcset=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-web-light.png\\\"><img alt=\\\"Fix in Web\\\" width=\\\"99\\\" height=\\\"28\\\" src=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-web-dark.png\\\"></picture></a></p>\\n\\n\\n\\n---\\nFile: cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go:209\\nAuthor: cursor[bot]\\nBody: ### OpenCode message count uses wrong JSONL line counting\\n\\n**High Severity**\\n\\n<!-- DESCRIPTION START -->\\n`countTranscriptItems` has no case for `AgentTypeOpenCode`, so it falls through to the JSONL line-counting branch (`strings.Split(content, \\\"\\\\n\\\")`). Since OpenCode transcripts are now a single JSON document, this returns the number of lines in the JSON blob rather than the number of messages. The result is assigned to `CheckpointTranscriptStart`, which is later passed to `opencode.SliceFromMessage` as a message index — causing wildly incorrect transcript scoping for multi-checkpoint sessions.\\n<!-- DESCRIPTION END -->\\n\\n<!-- BUGBOT_BUG_ID: ref2_9d32b0f3-6555-49cf-9e87-6072a725d46e -->\\n\\n<!-- LOCATIONS START\\ncmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go#L501-L527\\nLOCATIONS END -->\\n<p><a href=\\\"https://cursor.com/open?REDACTED\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\"><picture><source media=\\\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\\\" srcset=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-cursor-dark.png\\\"><source media=\\\"(prefers-color-scheme: light)\\\" srcset=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-cursor-light.png\\\"><img alt=\\\"Fix in Cursor\\\" width=\\\"115\\\" height=\\\"28\\\" src=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-cursor-dark.png\\\"></picture></a>&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://cursor.com/agents?REDACTED\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\"><picture><source media=\\\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\\\" srcset=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-web-dark.png\\\"><source media=\\\"(prefers-color-scheme: light)\\\" srcset=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-web-light.png\\\"><img alt=\\\"Fix in Web\\\" width=\\\"99\\\" height=\\\"28\\\" src=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-web-dark.png\\\"></picture></a></p>\\n\\n\\n\\n---\\nFile: cmd/entire/cli/agent/opencode/entire_plugin.ts:14\\nAuthor: cursor[bot]\\nBody: ### Unused partStore accumulates data with no consumers\\n\\n**Low Severity**\\n\\n<!-- DESCRIPTION START -->\\n`partStore` is populated on every `message.part.updated` event (with `findIndex`, replacement, and `Map.set` operations) and cleared on `session.deleted`, but its data is never read. All consumers (`writeTranscriptFromMemory`, `writeExportJSON`, `formatMessageFromStore`) were removed in this refactor, making the accumulation logic dead code that wastes CPU on every part event.\\n<!-- DESCRIPTION END